&gt; 
&gt; Based upon experience (i.e. Supervisor NEAT). And also, yes, it is
&gt; profoundly more effective to start with your best &quot;knowledge&quot; to
&gt; date, whether supervisor params or experiment results. This also
&gt; facilitates restarts rather than starting from scratch.
&gt; 
&gt; Your prediction that some bad parameters will be evolved is true, but
&gt; does not disprove the premise that some good parameters will also be
&gt; evolved. That is what the underlying NEAT concepts are adept at
&gt; dealing with.
&gt; 
&gt; Your suggested good experiment has already been performed many times
&gt; over. It required the ability for supervisor NEAT to drive experiment
&gt; NEAT, which as previously stated increases computational
&gt; requirements. This is why the need for exploitation of infant
&gt; populations to overcome what I call lateral genetic mobility
&gt; limitations. This coupled with the pyramid population vs. starting
&gt; genome complexity scheme has been utilized. Put the computational
&gt; bullets where they do the most good.
&gt; 
&gt; 
